For all of you complaining that Eleanor is "too fat" or just "fat" in 
general. please kindly shut up. Eleanor is written as a plus size girl, and 
yes it would be a huge and utter and heartbreaking disappointment if a 
movie did come out and she was played as a skinny girl or just one who's 
maybe pulling average but still pronounced as skinny. This book is supposed 
too give more bigger or average looking girls the sense that not every girl 
in a movie has too be in perfect shape with flawless skin and perfect hair 
to have someone find you beautiful, and eventually fall in love. Because 
believe me, that is not true, far from it. Mannequins may be all the same 
size but we, are not. So yes she's bigger, yes she doesn't have perfect 
skin. But that doesn't mean that that girl isn't still beautiful. It's how 
she was written and it's about time a movie like this finally came out. ﻿

Hey guys, I play eleanor in this trailer and I have some stuff to tell you 
guys. First of all, this is not the movie trailer and it was not for school 
it was for the national library program, yalsa, it was part of a contest. 
Second, I was completely in charge of planning everything for this video 
and we got it done in a month, my friend who plays park is actually half 
Korean and this was the first time he has ever acted and I thought he did a 
wonderful job. He didn't have time to grow his hair out or get colored 
contacts, or grow a couple inches so calm down. 3rd, I agreed to make this 
trailer before I read the book, and from the synopsis I cast myself as 
eleanor but as I read I didn't see me either, I too thought I was too fat. 
However, everyone always says, "you're your worst critic." Yeah, I thought 
that was the case until I read these comments. I know I'm obese you don't 
have to tell me. Some of these comments haunt me everyday and even more so 
they were what kick started my depression. I have thought about killing 
myself because of something you typed mindlessly. The ones that hurt me 
most are the ones that critique my acting. I am an actress and i work hard, 
I would like to peruse it as a career, but these comments make me question 
that. This has been a psa please stop the hate. I told myself that after a 
while I would stop caring, but I still do, please stop.﻿
